A.	CYBER CRIME CASE STUDY – 
Phishing is a type of online scam where people try to fool others and take their personal details like passwords, bank details, or OTPs. It usually happens through fake messages or emails that look real.
For example, a student may get a message saying it is from their bank. The message says there is a problem with their account and asks them to click on a link. When they click on the link, it opens a fake website that looks like the real one. The student enters their details without knowing it is fake, and their information gets stolen.
Many students become victims because these messages look real and create panic. The result can be loss of money or misuse of personal information.
So, it is important to stay careful and not trust every message or link on the internet.
B.	PREVENTION CHECKLIST-
Stay Safe:
•	Do not share OTP or password 
•	Do not click unknown links 
•	Check website before using it 
•	Use strong passwords 
•	Keep your phone/laptop safe 

